State of Connecticut v. Norman Dawkins (9019)

Dupont, C. J., Nokcott and Heiman, Js.

Argued June 11 decision released July 9, 1991 *810M. Donald Cardwell, for the appellant (defendant). Susan C. Marks, assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were JohnM. Bailey, state’s attorney, and Kevin P. McMahon, assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
